.TH "map_mft_record_page" 9 "map_mft_record_page" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
map_mft_record_page \- map the page in which a specific mft record resides
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "MFT_RECORD *" map_mft_record_page
.BI "(ntfs_inode *ni "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ni" 12
ntfs inode whose mft record page to map
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This maps the page in which the mft record of the ntfs inode \fIni\fP is situated
and returns a pointer to the mft record within the mapped page.

Return value needs to be checked with \fBIS_ERR\fP and if that is true \fBPTR_ERR\fP
contains the negative error code returned.
